article.headline: New Orleans 62, Arkansas State 58
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- James Parlow hit the go-ahead 3-pointer while Jacob Manning and Jeremie Davis each hit two free throws in the final 32.6 seconds to lead the University of New Orleans to a 62-58 Sun Belt Conference men's basketball victory Saturday over Arkansas State. Davis scored a game-high 20 points, while Manning added 13 for the Privateers (9-18, 6-9). Nathaniel Parker grabbed a game-high 11 rebounds in addition to the seven points he scored. Isaac Wells led the Indians (12-17, 7-7) with a double-double of 13 points and 11 rebounds, while Dereke Tipler scored 18 points and Yual Banks chipped in 12. After trailing 33-26 at intermission, New Orleans scored the first eight points of the second half, capped by a Manning basket at the 16:28 mark to give the Privateers their first lead of the contest at 34-33. That lead change was the first of seven over the final 20 minutes, which also included seven ties. The final tie of the game came at 55-55 after Banks hit a 3-pointer with 1:42 left. Banks then gave ASU its final lead at 57-55 when he made two-of-three free throws after being fouled by the Privateers' Dusty Driggs with 1:06 to play. On the next possession, Parlow made a jumper at the top of the key to give New Orleans the advantage for good.
